Yesterday, heaven gained the worlds most iconic, fire cracker, favorite grandma ever. Grandma, I will forever be speechless. I never wanted to believe this day would come. I would do anything just to hear my bedroom door open one more time while you walk into my room in the morning to check on me and tuck me back in. And even just hearing you say “clauuuddeeaaaa” (in your little accent). You lived 100 amazing years and I couldn’t be more grateful to have called you my grandma. You left a mark on everyone that got to know you, you were truly the best. I was extremely blessed to live with you for 17 years of my life and I wouldn’t change it for the world. The Ercolano household will never be the same without you here. I love you beyond words, grandma vicky. Until we meet again my angel, rest in the sweetest peace🤍🫶🏼🥺🕊♥️♠️♣️♦️🙏🏼
